Visited here for our first time and was disappointed.
Had seen an ad in a magazine and looked on the internet to check it out.
I really expected much much more.
Sandwiches were just OK.
In my opinion, nothing to brag about.
What really turned us off was the filth in this place.
EVERY table was sticky and had crumbs etc all over them.
The floor needed some serious attention, as did the trash receptacle.
It was not busy and there was sufficient help to tidy up.
It's a shame because I think they could make a "go" of it.

I'm not sure why all the bad reviews.
I've been coming here for 8 years and every time I have excellent food as well as great customer service.
The owner Dennis is always friendly.
The bread is delicious.
My favorites are the fiesta chicken and bbq chicken pizza.
Try it yourself!

